{
  "texts": [
    "SLPs must remember that predictive models offer probability and not certainty, and they should treat all outputs as hypotheses requiring falsification and clinical interpretation.",
    "AI's ability to translate across languages may decrease motivation to learn new languages, potentially eroding cultural awareness.",
    "Yet the same tools could strengthen preservation of low-resource and regional dialects, expanding inclusive care.",
    "AI is not a passing trend; it is a transformational force already reshaping healthcare.",
    "For SLPs, it represents an unprecedented opportunity to enhance diagnosis, treatment, and access to care, especially for multilingual and underserved communities."
  ]
}